file.name: openapi.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.0
info:
  version: 1.0.0
  title: Eventuate account manage example account-view service API
  license:
    name: MIT
servers:
  - url: 'http://light-eventuate.swagger.io/v1'
paths:
  /accounts:
    get:
      summary: Return list of account object with customer Id
      operationId: getAccountsByCustomerId
      tags:
        - accounts
      parameters:
        - name: customerId
          in: query
          description: customerId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string        
      security:
        - account_auth:
            - 'read:account'
            - 'write:account'
      responses:
        '200':
          description: Successful response
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetAccountResponse'
        '201':
          description: Null response
        default:
          description: unexpected error
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
  '/accounts/{accountId}':
    get:
      summary: get an account by accountId
      operationId: getAccountByAccpuntId
      tags:
        - accounts
      parameters:
        - name: accountId
          in: path
          required: true
          description: The id of the account
          schema:
            type: string
      security:
        - account_auth:
            - 'read:account'
            - 'write:account'
      responses:
        '200':
          description: Expected response to a valid request
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetAccountResponse'
        default:
          description: unexpected error
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
  '/accounts/{accountId}/history':
    get:
      summary: get Transactions History
      operationId: getAccountTransactionHistory
      tags:
        - accounts
      parameters:
        - name: accountId
          in: path
          description: accountId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      security:
        - account_auth:
            - 'read:account'
      responses:
        '200':
          description: List of accounts
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: array
                items:
                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/AccountTransactionInfo'
        default:
          description: unexpected error
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
components:
  securitySchemes:
    account_auth:
      type: oauth2
      description: This API uses OAuth 2 with the client credential grant flow.
      flows:
        clientCredentials:
          tokenUrl: 'https://localhost:6882/token'
          scopes:
            'write:account': modify account
            'read:account': read account
  schemas:
    AccountTransactionInfo:
      required:
        - fromAccountId
        - toAccountId
      properties:
        fromAccountId:
          type: string
        toAccountId:
          type: string
        transactionId:
          type: string
        amount:
          type: integer
          format: int32
    GetAccountResponse:
      required:
        - accountId
      properties:
        accountId:
          type: string
        title:
          type: string
        description:
          type: string
        balance:
          type: number
          format: double
    CreateTodoRequest:
      required:
        - title
      properties:
        title:
          type: string
        completed:
          type: boolean
        executionOrder:
          type: integer
          format: int32
    Error:
      required:
        - code
        - message
      properties:
        code:
          type: integer
          format: int32
        message:
          type: string
